1
00:00:07,625 --> 00:00:09,667
Girl: WATER.

2
00:00:09,709 --> 00:00:11,458
EARTH.

3
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,583
FIRE.

4
00:00:13,625 --> 00:00:16,417
AIR.

5
00:00:16,458 --> 00:00:20,083
LONG AGO, THE FOUR NATIONS
LIVED TOGETHER IN HARMONY.

6
00:00:20,125 --> 00:00:24,750
THEN EVERYTHING CHANGED
WHEN THE FIRE NATION ATTACKED.

7
00:00:24,792 --> 00:00:28,792
ONLY THE AVATAR,
MASTER OF ALL FOUR ELEMENTS,
COULD STOP THEM.

8
00:00:28,834 --> 00:00:32,500
BUT WHEN THE WORLD
NEEDED HIM MOST, HE VANISHED.

9
00:00:32,542 --> 00:00:37,917
A HUNDRED YEARS PASSED,
AND MY BROTHER AND I
DISCOVERED THE NEW AVATAR:
AN AIRBENDER NAMED AANG.

10
00:00:37,959 --> 00:00:40,208
AND ALTHOUGH
HIS AIRBENDING SKILLS ARE GREAT,

11
00:00:40,250 --> 00:00:43,625
HE HAS A LOT TO LEARN BEFORE
HE'S READY TO SAVE ANYONE.

12
00:00:43,667 --> 00:00:47,709
BUT I BELIEVE
AANG CAN SAVE THE WORLD.

13
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:50,750
♪

14
00:00:54,667 --> 00:00:55,959
Girl: APPA IS MISSING.

15
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,709
WE HOPE TO FIND HIM
IN BA SING SE.

16
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:02,333
PROFESSOR ZEI,
HEAD OF ANTHROPOLOGY
AT BA SING SE UNIVERSITY.

17
00:01:02,375 --> 00:01:07,583
THIS LIBRARY IS SAID TO CONTAIN
A<i> VAST</i> COLLECTION OF KNOWLEDGE.

18
00:01:07,625 --> 00:01:11,417
Boy: FIREBENDERS LOSE THEIR
BENDING DURING A SOLAR ECLIPSE!

19
00:01:11,458 --> 00:01:15,000
WE'VE GOTTA GET THIS
INFORMATION TO THE EARTH KING
AT BA SING SE.

20
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:18,750
HEY!

21
00:01:18,792 --> 00:01:21,000
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
FIREBENDING YOUR TEA?

22
00:01:21,041 --> 00:01:23,959
SO THE OLD GUY
HAD SOME HOT TEA, BIG DEAL.

23
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,542
HE HEATED IT HIMSELF.

24
00:01:25,583 --> 00:01:27,959
THOSE GUYS ARE FIREBENDERS.

25
00:01:34,458 --> 00:01:38,750
♪

26
00:01:46,834 --> 00:01:48,875
LOOK, THE INNER WALL.

27
00:01:51,959 --> 00:01:55,583
I CAN'T BELIEVE
WE FINALLY MADE IT
TO BA SING SE IN ONE PIECE.

28
00:01:55,625 --> 00:01:57,333
HEY, DON'T JINX IT!

29
00:01:57,375 --> 00:02:00,291
WE COULD STILL BE ATTACKED
BY SOME GIANT, EXPLODING
FIRE NATION SPOON.

30
00:02:00,333 --> 00:02:04,000
OR FIND OUT THE CITY'S
BEEN SUBMERGED IN AN OCEAN
FULL OF KILLER SHRIMP.

31
00:02:04,041 --> 00:02:06,291
YOU BEEN HITTING
THE CACTUS JUICE AGAIN?

32
00:02:06,333 --> 00:02:07,250
I'M JUST SAYIN'.

33
00:02:07,291 --> 00:02:08,458
WEIRD STUFF HAPPENS TO US.

34
00:02:11,417 --> 00:02:12,583
[SUCKING]

35
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:17,500
DON'T WORRY, AANG,
WE'LL FIND APPA.

36
00:02:17,542 --> 00:02:18,792
IT'S SUCH A BIG CITY.

37
00:02:18,834 --> 00:02:20,917
HE'S A GIANT BISON.

38
00:02:20,959 --> 00:02:22,792
WHERE COULD SOMEONE
POSSIBLY HIDE HIM?

39
00:02:30,917 --> 00:02:31,917
OH.

40
00:02:43,792 --> 00:02:45,583
Girl: AH, BACK IN THE CITY.

41
00:02:45,625 --> 00:02:46,500
GREAT.

42
00:02:46,542 --> 00:02:47,917
Boy: WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

43
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:49,291
IT'S AMAZING!

44
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:51,792
JUST A BUNCH OF WALLS AND RULES.

45
00:02:51,834 --> 00:02:55,291
YOU WAIT, YOU'LL GET SICK OF IT
IN A COUPLE OF DAYS.

46
00:03:00,417 --> 00:03:01,875
Aang: I'M COMIN' FOR YOU, BUDDY.

47
00:03:03,792 --> 00:03:05,375
HE'S HERE, I CAN FEEL IT.

48
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,208
HELLO, MY NAME IS JOO DEE.

49
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:21,583
I HAVE BEEN GIVEN
THE GREAT HONOR OF SHOWING
THE AVATAR AROUND BA SING SE.

50
00:03:21,625 --> 00:03:24,500
AND YOU MUST BE SOKKA,
KATARA AND TOPH.

51
00:03:24,542 --> 00:03:26,917
WELCOME TO OUR WONDERFUL CITY.

52
00:03:26,959 --> 00:03:29,542
SHALL WE GET STARTED?

53
00:03:29,583 --> 00:03:33,583
YES, WE HAVE INFORMATION ABOUT
THE FIRE NATION ARMY THAT
WE NEED TO DELIVER TO
THE EARTH KING IMMEDIATELY.

54
00:03:33,625 --> 00:03:35,583
GREAT, LET'S BEGIN OUR TOUR.

55
00:03:35,625 --> 00:03:38,500
AND THEN I'LL SHOW YOU
TO YOUR NEW HOME, HERE.

56
00:03:38,542 --> 00:03:41,208
I THINK YOU'LL LIKE IT.

57
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:42,542
AUGH!

58
00:03:42,583 --> 00:03:44,375
MAYBE YOU MISSED WHAT I SAID.

59
00:03:44,417 --> 00:03:47,500
WE NEED TO TALK TO THE KING
ABOUT THE WAR,
IT'S IMPORTANT.

60
00:03:47,542 --> 00:03:49,417
YOU'RE IN BA SING SE, NOW.

61
00:03:49,458 --> 00:03:51,417
EVERYONE IS SAFE HERE.

62
00:03:54,458 --> 00:03:56,458
Joo Dee: THIS IS THE LOWER RING.

63
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:59,250
WHAT'S THAT WALL FOR?

64
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:02,041
OH, BA SING SE HAS MANY WALLS.

65
00:04:02,083 --> 00:04:07,000
THERE ARE THE ONES OUTSIDE,
PROTECTING US,
AND THE ONES INSIDE,
THAT HELP MAINTAIN ORDER.

66
00:04:07,041 --> 00:04:10,125
THIS IS WHERE
OUR NEWEST ARRIVALS LIVE,

67
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:13,542
AS WELL AS OUR CRAFTSMEN
AND ARTISANS, PEOPLE THAT WORK
WITH THEIR HANDS.

68
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:15,709
IT'S SO QUAINT AND LIVELY.

69
00:04:18,667 --> 00:04:20,834
YOU<i> DO</i> WANT TO
WATCH YOUR STEP, THOUGH.

70
00:04:20,875 --> 00:04:25,667
WHY DO THEY HAVE ALL THESE
POOR PEOPLE BLOCKED OFF
IN ONE PART OF THE CITY?

71
00:04:25,709 --> 00:04:28,375
THIS IS WHY
I NEVER CAME HERE BEFORE.

72
00:04:28,417 --> 00:04:33,709
I ALWAYS HEARD IT WAS
SO DIFFERENT FROM THE WAY
THE MONKS TAUGHT US TO LIVE.

73
00:04:39,792 --> 00:04:46,125
I JUST WANT OUR NEW PLACE
TO LOOK NICE IN CASE SOMEONE
BRINGS HOME A LADY FRIEND.

74
00:04:46,166 --> 00:04:47,542
THIS CITY IS A PRISON.

75
00:04:47,583 --> 00:04:50,208
I DON'T WANT TO
MAKE A LIFE HERE.

76
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:54,125
Old Man: LIFE HAPPENS
WHEREVER YOU ARE,
WHETHER YOU MAKE IT OR NOT.

77
00:04:54,166 --> 00:04:59,709
NOW COME ON,
I FOUND US SOME NEW JOBS,
AND WE START THIS AFTERNOON.

78
00:05:01,417 --> 00:05:04,625
LOOK AT THEM,
FIREBENDERS LIVING
RIGHT UNDER EVERYONE'S NOSE.

79
00:05:07,083 --> 00:05:10,625
Girl: JET, YOU SAW A MAN
WITH A HOT CUP OF TEA.

80
00:05:10,667 --> 00:05:12,250
IT DOESN'T PROVE
HE'S A FIREBENDER.

81
00:05:12,291 --> 00:05:15,750
AND WHAT IF HE IS,
ARE WE SUPPOSED TO ATTACK THEM?

82
00:05:15,792 --> 00:05:19,000
I THOUGHT WE WERE STARTING OVER
HERE, CHANGING OUR WAYS.

83
00:05:19,041 --> 00:05:24,667
WE ARE, WHEN I GET THE EVIDENCE
I NEED, I'LL REPORT THEM
TO THE POLICE AND LET THEM
HANDLE IT, O.K.?

84
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:30,250
Joo Dee: THIS IS THE MIDDLE RING
OF BA SING SE,

85
00:05:30,291 --> 00:05:34,166
HOME TO THE FINANCIAL DISTRICT,
SHOPS AND RESTAURANTS
AND THE UNIVERSITY.

86
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:36,834
YEAH, WE MET A PROFESSOR
FROM BA SING SE UNIVERSITY.

87
00:05:36,875 --> 00:05:40,083
HE TOOK US TO
AN ANCIENT UNDERGROUND LIBRARY
WHERE WE DISCOVERED INFORMATION
ABOUT THE WAR

88
00:05:40,125 --> 00:05:42,583
THAT IS<i> ABSOLUTELY CRUCIAL</i>
<i>FOR THE KING TO HEAR</i> !

89
00:05:42,625 --> 00:05:45,208
ISN'T HISTORY FASCINATING?

90
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:49,500
LOOK, HERE'S ONE OF
THE OLDEST BUILDINGS
IN THE MIDDLE RING, TOWN HALL.

91
00:05:50,542 --> 00:05:52,083
IS THAT WOMAN DEAF?

92
00:05:52,125 --> 00:05:55,083
SHE ONLY SEEMS TO HEAR
EVERY OTHER WORD I SAY.

93
00:05:55,125 --> 00:05:56,250
IT'S CALLED BEING HANDLED.

94
00:05:56,291 --> 00:05:57,667
GET USED TO IT.

95
00:06:05,083 --> 00:06:08,375
WELL, YOU CERTAINLY LOOK LIKE
OFFICIAL TEA SERVERS.

96
00:06:08,417 --> 00:06:09,792
HOW DO YOU FEEL?

97
00:06:09,834 --> 00:06:11,709
RIDICULOUS.

98
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:15,333
UH, DOES THIS POSSIBLY COME IN
A LARGER SIZE?

99
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:17,667
I HAVE EXTRA STRING IN THE BACK.

100
00:06:17,709 --> 00:06:20,000
HAVE SOME TEA WHILE YOU WAIT.

101
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:25,959
EOW!

102
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,542
THIS TEA IS NOTHING MORE
THAN HOT LEAF JUICE!

103
00:06:29,583 --> 00:06:32,375
UNCLE, THAT'S WHAT<i> ALL</i> TEA IS.

104
00:06:32,417 --> 00:06:37,625
HOW COULD A MEMBER OF
MY OWN FAMILY SAY SOMETHING
SO HORRIBLE?

105
00:06:37,667 --> 00:06:41,208
WE'LL HAVE TO MAKE SOME
MAJOR CHANGES AROUND HERE.

106
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:41,959
[GASPING]

107
00:06:47,375 --> 00:06:51,250
Joo Dee: THE UPPER RING IS HOME
TO OUR MOST IMPORTANT CITIZENS.

108
00:06:51,291 --> 00:06:52,583
YOUR HOUSE
IS NOT TOO FAR FROM HERE.

109
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,834
WHAT'S INSIDE THAT WALL?

110
00:07:01,875 --> 00:07:04,417
AND WHO ARE
THE MEAN-LOOKING GUYS IN ROBES?

111
00:07:04,458 --> 00:07:06,750
INSIDE IS THE ROYAL PALACE.

112
00:07:06,792 --> 00:07:11,709
THOSE MEN ARE AGENTS OF
THE DAI LI, THE CULTURAL
AUTHORITY OF BA SING SE.

113
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:14,000
THEY ARE THE GUARDIANS
OF ALL OUR TRADITIONS.

114
00:07:14,041 --> 00:07:15,500
CAN WE SEE THE KING NOW?

115
00:07:15,542 --> 00:07:17,166
[LAUGHING] OH, NO!

116
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:19,750
ONE DOESN'T JUST POP IN
ON THE EARTH KING.

117
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:25,542
Joo Dee: HERE WE ARE,
YOUR NEW HOME.

118
00:07:29,041 --> 00:07:30,834
MORE GOOD NEWS.

119
00:07:30,875 --> 00:07:33,875
YOUR REQUEST FOR AN AUDIENCE
WITH THE EARTH KING
IS BEING PROCESSED,

120
00:07:33,917 --> 00:07:36,458
AND SHOULD BE PUT THROUGH
IN ABOUT A MONTH.

121
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,250
MUCH MORE QUICKLY THAN USUAL.

122
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:40,208
A MONTH?

123
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:43,834
SIX TO EIGHT WEEKS, ACTUALLY.

124
00:07:50,417 --> 00:07:51,709
Joo Dee: ISN'T IT NICE?

125
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:54,041
I THINK
YOU'LL REALLY ENJOY IT HERE.

126
00:07:54,083 --> 00:07:57,125
I THINK WE'D ENJOY IT MORE
IF WE WEREN'T STAYING SO LONG.

127
00:07:57,166 --> 00:07:59,375
CAN'T WE SEE THE KING
ANY SOONER?

128
00:07:59,417 --> 00:08:02,667
THE EARTH KING IS VERY BUSY
RUNNING THE FINEST CITY
IN THE WORLD,

129
00:08:02,709 --> 00:08:05,583
BUT HE WILL SEE YOU
AS SOON AS TIME PERMITS.

130
00:08:05,625 --> 00:08:09,208
IF WE'RE GONNA BE HERE
FOR A MONTH, WE SHOULD
SPEND OUR TIME LOOKING FOR APPA.

131
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:12,542
I'LL BE HAPPY TO ESCORT YOU
ANYWHERE YOU'D LIKE TO GO.

132
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:14,667
WE DON'T NEED A BABYSITTER.

133
00:08:14,709 --> 00:08:17,000
OH, I WON'T GET IN THE WAY.

134
00:08:17,041 --> 00:08:20,375
AND TO LEAVE YOU ALONE
WOULD MAKE ME A BAD HOST.

135
00:08:20,417 --> 00:08:22,667
WHERE SHALL WE START?

136
00:08:25,166 --> 00:08:26,667
[CHIRPING]

137
00:08:26,709 --> 00:08:29,125
[SCREECHING]

138
00:08:29,166 --> 00:08:32,125
I'M SORRY, BUT I HAVEN'T HEARD
ANYTHING ABOUT A FLYING BISON.

139
00:08:32,166 --> 00:08:34,750
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
THERE WERE ANY.

140
00:08:34,792 --> 00:08:38,625
IF SOMEONE WANTED TO SELL
A STOLEN ANIMAL WITHOUT ANYONE
KNOWING, WHERE WOULD THEY GO?

141
00:08:38,667 --> 00:08:40,041
WHERE'S THE BLACK MARKET?

142
00:08:40,083 --> 00:08:40,834
WHO RUNS IT?

143
00:08:40,875 --> 00:08:42,458
COME ON, YOU KNOW.

144
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:43,542
UH...

145
00:08:46,542 --> 00:08:49,792
THAT WOULD BE ILLEGAL.

146
00:08:49,834 --> 00:08:51,583
YOU'LL HAVE TO LEAVE NOW.

147
00:08:51,625 --> 00:08:53,166
YOUR LEMUR IS HARASSING
MY SPARROWKEETS.

148
00:08:58,542 --> 00:09:01,917
Boy: HMM, I'VE NEVER SEEN
ANY SANDBENDERS OR NOMADS
AROUND HERE.

149
00:09:01,959 --> 00:09:05,625
YOU SHOULD ASK PROFESSOR ZEI,
HE TEACHES THE CLASS
ON DESERT CULTURES.

150
00:09:05,667 --> 00:09:07,625
RIGHT.

151
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:13,875
AND WHICH OF YOUR PROFESSORS
COULD WE ASK ABOUT THE WAR
WITH THE FIRE NATION?

152
00:09:13,917 --> 00:09:18,000
I DON'T KNOW, I'M NOT
A POLITICAL SCIENCE STUDENT,
I HAVE TO GET TO CLASS.

153
00:09:18,041 --> 00:09:19,875
UNH!

154
00:09:23,166 --> 00:09:26,417
Joo Dee: WELL, I'M SORRY NO ONE
HAS SEEN YOUR BISON.

155
00:09:26,458 --> 00:09:28,625
WHY DON'T YOU GO GET SOME REST?

156
00:09:28,667 --> 00:09:29,750
SOMEONE WILL BE OVER
WITH DINNER LATER.

157
00:09:37,917 --> 00:09:38,625
HEY, COME WITH ME.

158
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:46,250
YOU'RE THE AVATAR.

159
00:09:46,291 --> 00:09:48,041
I HEARD YOU WERE IN TOWN.

160
00:09:48,083 --> 00:09:49,500
I'M PONG.

161
00:09:49,542 --> 00:09:50,959
NICE TO MEET YOU, PONG.

162
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,458
SO, PONG, WHAT'S GOIN' ON
WITH THIS CITY?

163
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:56,500
WHY IS EVERYONE HERE
SO SCARED TO TALK ABOUT THE WAR?

164
00:09:56,542 --> 00:09:57,667
WAR, SCARED?

165
00:09:57,709 --> 00:09:58,917
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

166
00:09:58,959 --> 00:10:00,959
I CAN FEEL YOU SHAKING.

167
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:04,041
LOOK, I'M JUST
A MINOR GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL.

168
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:06,583
I'VE WAITED THREE YEARS
TO GET THIS HOUSE.

169
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:08,458
I DON'T WANT TO
GET INTO TROUBLE.

170
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,500
GET IN TROUBLE WITH WHO?

171
00:10:10,542 --> 00:10:13,583
SHH, LISTEN, YOU CAN'T
MENTION THE WAR, HERE.

172
00:10:13,625 --> 00:10:17,500
AND WHATEVER YOU DO,
STAY AWAY FROM THE DAI LI.

173
00:10:22,917 --> 00:10:25,709
Old Man: WOULD YOU LIKE
A POT OF TEA?

174
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:28,792
Young Man: WE'VE BEEN WORKING
IN A TEA SHOP ALL DAY.

175
00:10:28,834 --> 00:10:30,917
I'M SICK OF TEA.

176
00:10:30,959 --> 00:10:33,000
SICK OF TEA?

177
00:10:33,041 --> 00:10:36,792
THAT'S LIKE BEING
SICK OF BREATHING.

178
00:10:36,834 --> 00:10:39,959
HAVE YOU SEEN OUR SPARK ROCKS
TO HEAT UP THE WATER?

179
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,500
THEY'RE NOT THERE.

180
00:10:42,542 --> 00:10:44,959
YOU'LL HAVE TO FIREBEND,
OLD MAN.

181
00:10:47,166 --> 00:10:49,000
Jet: WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

182
00:10:49,041 --> 00:10:52,583
Old Man: I BORROWED
OUR NEIGHBOR'S.

183
00:10:52,625 --> 00:10:53,625
SUCH KIND PEOPLE.

184
00:10:59,041 --> 00:11:03,083
[CHIRPING]

185
00:11:03,125 --> 00:11:06,583
[YAWNING]

186
00:11:08,166 --> 00:11:09,000
[GASPING]

187
00:11:09,417 --> 00:11:10,583
I'VE GOT IT!

188
00:11:10,625 --> 00:11:12,834
I KNOW HOW
WE'RE GONNA SEE THE EARTH KING.

189
00:11:12,875 --> 00:11:14,667
HOW'RE WE SUPPOSED TO DO THAT?

190
00:11:14,709 --> 00:11:17,583
"ONE DOESN'T JUST<i> POP IN</i>
ON THE EARTH KING."

191
00:11:17,625 --> 00:11:21,583
THE KING IS HAVING A PARTY
AT THE PALACE TONIGHT
FOR HIS PET BEAR.

192
00:11:21,625 --> 00:11:22,500
YOU MEAN PLATYPUS-BEAR?

193
00:11:22,542 --> 00:11:24,583
NO, IT JUST SAYS "BEAR."

194
00:11:24,625 --> 00:11:26,834
CERTAINLY YOU MEAN
HIS PET SKUNK-BEAR.

195
00:11:26,875 --> 00:11:28,250
OR HIS ARMADILLO-BEAR.

196
00:11:28,291 --> 00:11:29,417
GOPHER-BEAR?

197
00:11:29,458 --> 00:11:32,792
JUST "BEAR."

198
00:11:32,834 --> 00:11:35,083
THIS PLACE IS<i> WEIRD</i> .

199
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:36,417
THE PALACE WILL BE PACKED.

200
00:11:36,458 --> 00:11:38,458
WE CAN SNEAK IN WITH A CROWD.

201
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:39,250
WON'T WORK.

202
00:11:39,291 --> 00:11:40,542
WHY NOT?

203
00:11:40,583 --> 00:11:42,750
WELL, NO OFFENSE
TO YOU SIMPLE COUNTRY FOLK,

204
00:11:42,792 --> 00:11:45,959
BUT A REAL SOCIETY CROWD
WOULD SPOT YOU A MILE AWAY.

205
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,417
YOU'VE GOT NO MANNERS.

206
00:11:47,458 --> 00:11:49,500
EXCUSE ME?

207
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:51,417
<i>I'VE</i> GOT NO MANNERS?

208
00:11:51,458 --> 00:11:54,208
YOU'RE NOT EXACTLY
LADY FANCY FINGERS.

209
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:55,875
Toph: [BURPING]

210
00:11:55,917 --> 00:11:59,291
I LEARNED PROPER SOCIETY
BEHAVIOR AND<i> CHOSE</i> TO LEAVE IT.

211
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:01,125
YOU NEVER LEARNED ANYTHING.

212
00:12:01,166 --> 00:12:03,542
AND FRANKLY,
IT'S A LITTLE TOO LATE.

213
00:12:03,583 --> 00:12:05,291
AH-HA, BUT YOU LEARNED IT!

214
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:06,667
YOU COULD TEACH US.

215
00:12:06,709 --> 00:12:08,208
YEAH, I'M MASTERING
EVERY ELEMENT.

216
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:09,500
HOW HARD CAN MANNERS BE?

217
00:12:10,792 --> 00:12:13,375
"GOOD EVENING,
MR. SOKKA WATER TRIBE.

218
00:12:13,417 --> 00:12:15,333
MISS KATARA WATER TRIBE.

219
00:12:15,375 --> 00:12:19,500
LORD MOMO OF THE MOMO DYNASTY,
YOUR MOMO-NESS."

220
00:12:19,542 --> 00:12:22,834
"AVATAR AANG, HOW YOU<i> DO</i> GO ON."

221
00:12:27,208 --> 00:12:28,208
Aang: OW!

222
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:30,667
KATARA MIGHT BE ABLE TO
PULL IT OFF,

223
00:12:30,709 --> 00:12:33,542
BUT YOU TWO WOULD BE LUCKY
TO PASS AS BUSBOYS.

224
00:12:33,583 --> 00:12:35,542
BUT I FEEL SO FANCY.

225
00:12:39,166 --> 00:12:40,333
Aang: EARTH!
Sokka: FIRE!

226
00:12:40,375 --> 00:12:42,959
AUGH.

227
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:43,917
OOH.

228
00:12:48,166 --> 00:12:49,125
[GIGGLING]

229
00:12:49,166 --> 00:12:52,041
WOW, YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

230
00:12:53,667 --> 00:12:55,583
DON'T TALK TO
THE COMMONERS, KATARA.

231
00:12:55,625 --> 00:12:57,625
FIRST RULE OF SOCIETY.

232
00:12:57,667 --> 00:13:01,083
WE'LL GET IN THE PARTY
AND THEN FIND A WAY TO LET YOU
IN THROUGH THE SIDE GATE.

233
00:13:04,542 --> 00:13:05,625
[GONG RINGING]

234
00:13:16,458 --> 00:13:18,333
Girl: JET, WE NEED TO TALK.

235
00:13:18,375 --> 00:13:19,125
WHAT?

236
00:13:19,166 --> 00:13:20,291
OH, GREAT, IT'S YOU GUYS.

237
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,667
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

238
00:13:21,709 --> 00:13:24,083
I COULD USE SOME HELP
WITH SURVEILLANCE HERE.

239
00:13:24,125 --> 00:13:27,500
Girl: WE'VE BEEN TALKING,
AND WE THINK YOU'RE BECOMING
OBSESSED WITH THIS.

240
00:13:27,542 --> 00:13:28,417
IT'S NOT HEALTHY.

241
00:13:28,458 --> 00:13:29,458
OH, REALLY?

242
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:30,625
YOU BOTH THINK THIS?

243
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:34,417
WE CAME HERE
TO MAKE A FRESH START.

244
00:13:34,458 --> 00:13:36,208
BUT YOU WON'T LET THIS GO.

245
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:37,875
EVEN THOUGH
THERE'S NO REAL PROOF!

246
00:13:37,917 --> 00:13:39,667
WELL, MAYBE IF YOU'D HELP ME.

247
00:13:39,709 --> 00:13:41,333
JET, YOU'VE GOTTA STOP THIS.

248
00:13:41,375 --> 00:13:44,166
MAYBE YOU'VE FORGOTTEN WHY WE
NEED TO START OVER.

249
00:13:44,208 --> 00:13:47,709
MAYBE YOU'VE FORGOTTEN
ABOUT HOW THE FIRE NATION
LEFT US ALL HOMELESS?

250
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:50,625
HOW THEY WIPED OUT
ALL THE PEOPLE WE LOVED?

251
00:13:50,667 --> 00:13:54,291
IF YOU DON'T WANNA HELP ME,
I'LL GET THE EVIDENCE ON MY OWN.

252
00:14:00,625 --> 00:14:02,750
THIS IS THE BEST TEA
IN THE CITY.

253
00:14:02,792 --> 00:14:06,750
THE SECRET INGREDIENT IS LOVE.

254
00:14:10,959 --> 00:14:13,667
I THINK YOU'RE DUE FOR A RAISE.

255
00:14:16,208 --> 00:14:17,709
I'M TIRED OF WAITING.

256
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:20,166
THESE TWO MEN ARE FIREBENDERS!

257
00:14:30,208 --> 00:14:32,083
I KNOW THEY'RE FIREBENDERS!

258
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:34,041
I SAW THE OLD MAN
HEATING HIS TEA.

259
00:14:34,083 --> 00:14:36,041
HE WORKS IN A TEA SHOP.

260
00:14:36,083 --> 00:14:38,166
HE'S A FIREBENDER,
I'M TELLING YOU!

261
00:14:38,208 --> 00:14:41,125
DROP YOUR SWORDS, BOY,
NICE AND EASY.

262
00:14:41,917 --> 00:14:43,250
YOU'LL HAVE TO DEFEND YOURSELF.

263
00:14:43,291 --> 00:14:45,083
THEN EVERYONE WILL KNOW.

264
00:14:45,125 --> 00:14:47,208
GO AHEAD, SHOW THEM
WHAT YOU CAN DO.

265
00:14:48,959 --> 00:14:50,083
YOU WANT A SHOW?

266
00:14:50,125 --> 00:14:50,959
I'LL GIVE YOU A SHOW.

267
00:15:12,875 --> 00:15:13,625
Man: INVITATION, PLEASE.

268
00:15:13,667 --> 00:15:15,375
I THINK THIS WILL DO.

269
00:15:15,417 --> 00:15:17,834
NO ENTRY WITHOUT AN INVITATION.

270
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:19,583
STEP OUT OF LINE, PLEASE.

271
00:15:19,625 --> 00:15:23,291
LOOK, THE PANGS
AND THE YUMSOON-HANS
ARE WAITING IN THERE FOR US.

272
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:26,250
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
TELL THEM WHO DIDN'T LET ME IN.

273
00:15:26,291 --> 00:15:27,125
STEP OUT OF LINE, PLEASE.

274
00:15:38,041 --> 00:15:39,709
Katara: SIR?

275
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:43,291
I'M SORRY TO BOTHER YOU, BUT MY
COUSIN LOST OUR INVITATIONS.

276
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:44,834
[WHISPERING] SHE'S BLIND.

277
00:15:44,875 --> 00:15:47,375
DO YOU THINK YOU COULD HELP US?

278
00:15:47,417 --> 00:15:50,083
OUR FAMILY'S INSIDE, AND
I'M SURE THEY'RE VERY WORRIED.

279
00:15:50,125 --> 00:15:51,250
I AM HONORED.

280
00:15:51,291 --> 00:15:53,500
PLEASE COME WITH ME.

281
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:00,583
NYAA.
[BLOWING RASPBERRY]

282
00:16:05,041 --> 00:16:07,000
HE'S TAKING ALL THE GOOD STUFF.

283
00:16:07,041 --> 00:16:11,083
QUIET, YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT I HAD TO DO TO GET SEATS
THIS NEAR THE BEAR.

284
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:18,291
IT'S BEAUTIFUL, ISN'T IT?

285
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:21,041
BY THE WAY, I'M LONG FENG.

286
00:16:21,083 --> 00:16:22,959
I'M A CULTURAL MINISTER
TO THE KING.

287
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:27,834
I'M HWAMEI, AND THIS IS DUNG.

288
00:16:27,875 --> 00:16:28,625
OW!

289
00:16:28,667 --> 00:16:30,000
NOW WHERE IS YOUR FAMILY?

290
00:16:30,041 --> 00:16:31,875
I'D LOVE TO MEET THEM.

291
00:16:31,917 --> 00:16:35,667
UH, I DON'T SEE 'EM RIGHT NOW,
BUT I'M SURE
WE'LL FIND THEM SOON.

292
00:16:35,709 --> 00:16:37,417
THANKS FOR ALL YOUR HELP.

293
00:16:40,709 --> 00:16:46,917
DON'T WORRY, AS YOUR ESCORT,
IT WOULD BE DISHONORABLE
TO ABANDON YOU LADIES WITHOUT
FINDING YOUR FAMILY, FIRST.

294
00:16:46,959 --> 00:16:48,333
WE'LL KEEP LOOKING.

295
00:16:50,917 --> 00:16:52,417
WHERE ARE THEY?

296
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:55,000
LOOK, I CAME UP
WITH A BACK-UP PLAN.

297
00:16:55,041 --> 00:16:57,667
WE DRESS MOMO
LIKE A GHOST, O.K.?

298
00:16:57,709 --> 00:17:00,083
HE FLIES BY THE GUARDS,
CREATING A DISTRACTION.

299
00:17:00,125 --> 00:17:02,542
THEN WE BLAST A HOLE
IN THE WALL...

300
00:17:02,583 --> 00:17:05,125
OR WE CAN GO IN WITH THESE GUYS.

301
00:17:05,166 --> 00:17:07,291
Aang: TOPH SAID
WE MIGHT PASS AS BUSBOYS.

302
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:10,375
O.K., BUT REMEMBER
THAT MOMO GHOST PLAN.

303
00:17:10,417 --> 00:17:11,959
I THINK IT'S A WINNER.

304
00:17:13,625 --> 00:17:15,542
UGH!

305
00:17:15,583 --> 00:17:17,125
[GRUNTING]

306
00:17:17,166 --> 00:17:19,125
YOU MUST BE GETTING TIRED OF
USING THOSE SWORDS.

307
00:17:19,166 --> 00:17:22,000
WHY DON'T YOU GO AHEAD
AND FIREBEND AT ME?

308
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:24,125
PLEASE, SON, YOU'RE CONFUSED!

309
00:17:24,166 --> 00:17:25,959
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING!

310
00:17:27,041 --> 00:17:31,000
Jet: BET YOU WISH HE HELPED YOU
OUT WITH A LITTLE FIRE BLAST
RIGHT NOW.

311
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:32,917
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO NEEDS HELP.

312
00:17:42,458 --> 00:17:43,750
YOU SEE THAT?

313
00:17:43,792 --> 00:17:45,834
THE FIRE NATION
IS TRYING TO SILENCE ME!

314
00:17:45,875 --> 00:17:47,750
IT'LL NEVER HAPPEN.

315
00:17:47,792 --> 00:17:48,625
[GRUNTING]

316
00:17:53,166 --> 00:17:54,834
WHERE ARE TOPH AND KATARA?

317
00:17:54,875 --> 00:17:58,875
FORGET ABOUT THEM, JUST KEEP
AN EYE OUT FOR THE KING.

318
00:17:58,917 --> 00:18:01,125
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HE LOOKS LIKE.

319
00:18:01,166 --> 00:18:04,542
YOU KNOW, ROYAL,
FLOWING ROBE, FANCY JEWELRY.

320
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,625
Aang: THAT COULD BE ANYONE.

321
00:18:07,667 --> 00:18:10,291
ANOTHER CRAB PUFF, PLEASE.

322
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:11,959
YOU FOUND US!

323
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:15,125
I'D KNOW YOUR LITTLE FOOTSTEPS
ANYWHERE, TWINKLE TOES.

324
00:18:15,166 --> 00:18:16,917
THANKS FOR LETTING US IN.

325
00:18:16,959 --> 00:18:21,041
SORRY, BUT THE GUY
WHO ESCORTED US IN
WON'T LET US OUT OF HIS SIGHT.

326
00:18:21,083 --> 00:18:22,083
WHAT GUY?

327
00:18:23,542 --> 00:18:25,250
Joo Dee: WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

328
00:18:25,291 --> 00:18:28,792
YOU HAVE TO LEAVE IMMEDIATELY,
OR WE'LL ALL BE
IN TERRIBLE TROUBLE.

329
00:18:28,834 --> 00:18:30,917
NOT UNTIL WE SEE THE KING.

330
00:18:30,959 --> 00:18:32,166
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

331
00:18:32,208 --> 00:18:33,166
YOU MUST GO.

332
00:18:34,875 --> 00:18:36,750
Woman: [SCREAMING]

333
00:18:36,792 --> 00:18:37,917
OH!

334
00:18:37,959 --> 00:18:39,250
Aang: SORRY, NO, DON'T SHOUT.

335
00:18:44,959 --> 00:18:46,166
THE AVATAR.

336
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:49,667
OH, I DIDN'T KNOW
THE AVATAR WOULD BE HERE.

337
00:18:57,667 --> 00:18:59,000
[LAUGHING WEAKLY]

338
00:18:59,041 --> 00:19:01,542
YOU KEEP THEIR ATTENTION
WHILE I LOOK FOR THE KING.

339
00:19:01,583 --> 00:19:02,792
WATCH THIS, EVERYBODY.

340
00:19:11,041 --> 00:19:12,917
Crowd: OOH...

341
00:19:12,959 --> 00:19:14,458
[APPLAUSE]

342
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,959
[LAUGHING/GROWLING]

343
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:16,917
[GRUNTING]

344
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:28,291
DROP YOUR WEAPONS.

345
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:30,917
ARREST THEM,
THEY'RE FIREBENDERS.

346
00:19:30,959 --> 00:19:33,000
THIS POOR BOY IS CONFUSED.

347
00:19:33,041 --> 00:19:36,333
WE'RE JUST SIMPLE REFUGEES.

348
00:19:36,375 --> 00:19:41,041
THIS YOUNG MAN
WRECKED MY TEA SHOP
AND ASSAULTED MY EMPLOYEES!

349
00:19:41,083 --> 00:19:41,875
IT'S TRUE, SIR.

350
00:19:41,917 --> 00:19:43,458
WE SAW THE WHOLE THING.

351
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:46,625
THIS CRAZY KID
ATTACKED THE FINEST TEA MAKER
IN THE CITY.

352
00:19:46,667 --> 00:19:49,709
OH, THAT'S VERY SWEET.

353
00:19:50,083 --> 00:19:51,250
COME WITH US, SON.

354
00:19:53,208 --> 00:19:54,333
[GRUNTING]

355
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:57,583
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND!

356
00:19:57,625 --> 00:19:59,041
THEY'RE FIRE NATION!

357
00:19:59,083 --> 00:20:00,542
YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE ME.

358
00:20:31,041 --> 00:20:32,625
AANG, THE EARTH KING.

359
00:20:36,375 --> 00:20:37,542
GREETINGS, YOUR MAJESTY.

360
00:20:37,583 --> 00:20:38,375
[GASPING]
[GASPING]
[GASPING]

361
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:48,291
AUGH, UGH, LET ME GO!

362
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:52,625
[MUFFLED SHOUT]

363
00:20:52,667 --> 00:20:53,333
[MUFFLED SHOUT]

364
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:58,834
[CHIRPING]

365
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:04,000
AVATAR, IT IS A GREAT HONOR
TO MEET YOU.

366
00:21:04,041 --> 00:21:08,500
I AM LONG FENG,
GRAND SECRETARIAT OF BA SING SE
AND HEAD OF THE DAI LI.

367
00:21:08,542 --> 00:21:10,500
I'D LIKE TO TALK TO YOU.

368
00:21:10,542 --> 00:21:12,375
YOUR FRIENDS WILL BE
WAITING FOR US IN THE LIBRARY.

369
00:21:16,959 --> 00:21:18,917
Sokka: WHY WON'T YOU LET US
TALK TO THE KING?

370
00:21:18,959 --> 00:21:21,792
WE HAVE INFORMATION THAT COULD
DEFEAT THE FIRE NATION!

371
00:21:21,834 --> 00:21:25,792
Long Feng: THE EARTH KING
HAS NO TIME TO GET INVOLVED
WITH POLITICAL SQUABBLES

372
00:21:25,834 --> 00:21:28,166
AND THE DAY-TO-DAY MINUTIA
OF MILITARY ACTIVITIES.

373
00:21:28,208 --> 00:21:31,667
Aang: THIS COULD BE THE MOST
IMPORTANT THING HE'S EVER HEARD.

374
00:21:31,709 --> 00:21:37,458
WHAT'S MOST IMPORTANT TO HIS
ROYAL MAJESTY IS MAINTAINING THE
<i>CULTURAL</i> HERITAGE OF BA SING SE.

375
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:40,834
ALL HIS DUTIES RELATE TO
ISSUING DECREES ON SUCH MATTERS.

376
00:21:40,875 --> 00:21:45,375
IT'S<i> MY</i> JOB TO OVERSEE THE REST
OF THE CITY'S RESOURCES,
INCLUDING THE MILITARY.

377
00:21:45,417 --> 00:21:48,208
SO THE KING
IS JUST A FIGUREHEAD.

378
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:49,417
HE'S YOUR PUPPET.

379
00:21:49,458 --> 00:21:51,625
OH, NO, NO.

380
00:21:51,667 --> 00:21:55,333
HIS MAJESTY IS AN ICON,
A GOD TO HIS PEOPLE.

381
00:21:55,375 --> 00:21:59,583
HE CAN'T SULLY HIS HANDS
WITH THE HOURLY CHANGES
OF AN ENDLESS WAR.

382
00:21:59,625 --> 00:22:03,667
BUT WE FOUND OUT ABOUT
A SOLAR ECLIPSE THAT WILL LEAVE
THE FIRE NATION DEFENSELESS.

383
00:22:03,709 --> 00:22:05,166
YOU COULD LEAD AN INVASION...

384
00:22:05,208 --> 00:22:08,125
ENOUGH, I DON'T WANT TO HEAR
YOUR RIDICULOUS PLAN.

385
00:22:08,166 --> 00:22:13,709
IT IS THE STRICT POLICY
OF BA SING SE THAT THE WAR NOT
BE MENTIONED WITHIN THE WALLS.

386
00:22:13,750 --> 00:22:19,125
CONSTANT NEWS OF
AN ESCALATING WAR WILL THROW
THE CITIZENS OF BA SING SE
INTO A STATE OF PANIC.

387
00:22:19,166 --> 00:22:21,250
YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE ME,
THEY'RE FIREBENDERS.

388
00:22:21,291 --> 00:22:24,291
THEY WON'T STOP
UNTIL THEY WIN THE WAR.

389
00:22:24,333 --> 00:22:26,583
CALM DOWN, YOU'RE SAFE NOW.

390
00:22:29,792 --> 00:22:35,291
OUR ECONOMY WOULD BE RUINED,
OUR PEACEFUL WAY OF LIFE,
OUR TRADITIONS WOULD DISAPPEAR.

391
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:38,458
THERE'S NO WAR IN BA SING SE.

392
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:40,208
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

393
00:22:40,250 --> 00:22:42,667
WHERE DO YOU THINK
ALL THE REFUGEES COME FROM?

394
00:22:42,709 --> 00:22:44,875
YOU CAN'T HIDE IT.

395
00:22:44,917 --> 00:22:49,291
IN SILENCING TALK OF CONFLICT,
BA SING SE REMAINS
A PEACEFUL, ORDERLY UTOPIA.

396
00:22:49,333 --> 00:22:52,542
THE LAST ONE ON EARTH.

397
00:22:52,583 --> 00:22:54,667
[MUFFLED GRUNTING]

398
00:22:54,709 --> 00:22:57,750
THERE IS NO WAR
WITHIN THE WALLS.

399
00:22:57,792 --> 00:22:59,500
HERE WE ARE SAFE.

400
00:22:59,542 --> 00:23:01,834
HERE WE ARE FREE.

401
00:23:04,041 --> 00:23:06,750
YOU CAN'T KEEP THE TRUTH
FROM ALL THESE PEOPLE.

402
00:23:06,792 --> 00:23:08,000
THEY HAVE TO KNOW.

403
00:23:08,041 --> 00:23:09,333
I'LL TELL THEM.

404
00:23:09,375 --> 00:23:10,875
I'LL MAKE SURE EVERYONE KNOWS.

405
00:23:10,917 --> 00:23:13,542
UNTIL NOW, YOU'VE BEEN TREATED
AS OUR HONORED GUEST.

406
00:23:13,583 --> 00:23:17,583
BUT FROM NOW ON, YOU WILL BE
WATCHED EVERY MOMENT
BY DAI LI AGENTS.

407
00:23:17,625 --> 00:23:21,959
IF YOU MENTION THE WAR
TO ANYONE, YOU WILL BE EXPELLED
FROM THE CITY.

408
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:24,625
I UNDERSTAND YOU'VE BEEN
LOOKING FOR YOUR BISON.

409
00:23:24,667 --> 00:23:29,083
IT WOULD BE QUITE A SHAME
IF YOU WERE NOT ABLE
TO COMPLETE YOUR QUEST.

410
00:23:29,125 --> 00:23:31,959
NOW JOO DEE WILL SHOW YOU HOME.

411
00:23:34,542 --> 00:23:36,041
Woman: COME WITH ME, PLEASE.

412
00:23:36,083 --> 00:23:37,917
WHAT HAPPENED TO JOO DEE?

413
00:23:37,959 --> 00:23:39,417
I'M JOO DEE.

414
00:23:39,458 --> 00:23:42,417
I'LL BE YOUR HOST AS LONG
AS YOU'RE IN OUR WONDERFUL CITY.

415
00:23:52,834 --> 00:23:55,834
♪
